---
import Layout from '../../layouts/main.astro';

const lang: string = 'en';
---

<Layout title="Books" lang={lang}>
  <section class="relative z-20 max-w-2xl mx-auto my-10 px-7 lg:px-0">
    <div class="content mt-10">
      <h2 class="font-laomn small-caps text-neutral-600 text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">
        Tener un cuerpo es mala poesía
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start mb-16">
        <!-- Left column - Book cover -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
          <img src="/assets/images/books/book-1.png" alt="Book cover" class="w-full h-auto shadow-lg" />
        </div>

        <!-- Right column - Book content -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="mb-7">
              <p class="text-neutral-600"><b>Emilio Prados International Poetry Prize (2024)</b></p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Children pulling each other's hair, The Simpsons, kisses with strangers, screams in the house... This book
              is a flicker of biographical lightning. Here, literature illuminates a body, darkens it, and illuminates
              it again. Past and present, pleasure and pain, confession and mockery of that confession; reading these
              poems is to be swept away by a swing of unusual images. To write his story, the author uses resources
              apparently foreign to poetry, because he knows that nothing is foreign to it.
            </p>
            <div>
              <p class="font-laomn small-caps text-2xl w-full text-center font-bold text-red-700 mb-2 tracking-wide">
                Buy
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-row gap-4 mt-6 items-center justify-center">
                <a
                  href="https://libreriasiglo.com/245809-tener-un-cuerpo-es-mala-poesia"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="font-laomn inline-block px-8 py-2 bg-red-600 text-white font-serif font-semibold transition hover:bg-red-700 text-center shadow"
                >
                  Colombia
                </a>
                <a
                  href="https://pre-textos.com/producto/tener-un-cuerpo-es-mala-poesia/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="font-laomninline-block px-8 py-2 bg-red-600 text-white font-serif font-semibold transition hover:bg-red-700 text-center shadow"
                >
                  International
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-laomn small-caps text-neutral-600 text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">
        Coordenadas de un plano irrealizable
      </h2>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start mb-10">
        <!-- Left column - Book cover -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
          <img src="/assets/images/books/book-2.png" alt="Book cover" class="w-full h-auto shadow-lg" />

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="font-laomn small-caps text-2xl w-full text-center font-bold text-red-700 mb-2 tracking-wide">
              Buy
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-row gap-4 mt-6 items-center justify-center">
              <a
                href="https://libreriasiglo.com/119664-coordenadas-de-un-plano-irrealizable"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="font-laomn inline-block px-8 py-2 bg-red-600 text-white font-serif font-semibold transition hover:bg-red-700 text-center shadow"
              >
                Colombia
              </a>
              <a
                href="https://pre-textos.com/producto/coordenadas-de-un-plano-irrealizable/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="font-laomn inline-block px-8 py-2 bg-red-600 text-white font-serif font-semibold transition hover:bg-red-700 text-center shadow"
              >
                International
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right column - Book content -->
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-7">
              <div>
                <p class="text-neutral-600">
                  <b>Radio Nacional de España-Fundación Montemadrid Young Poetry Prize (2021)</b>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-neutral-600">
                  <b>Finalist for the National Poetry Prize of the Ministry of Culture of Colombia (2023)</b>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="">
                <p class="">
                  "In this book, poetry is an animal that peers into the cave of the mouth to search for the word that
                  is missing to build the house and that will continue to be missing so that literature does not become
                  extinct."
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2">—Gina Saraceni</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p>
                  "Sebastián Martínez Vanegas has written one of the most unique poetry books we have read recently in
                  Colombia."
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2">—David Marín-Hincapié</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p>
                  "At just 27 years old, the author, with language that knots together enigma and high precision,
                  constructs from the cracking and collapse of the house a perplexing metaphor of abandonment and the
                  ruin of the world as a dwelling, and of the very cracked voice that names it."
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2">
                  —Statements about the finalists of the National Poetry Prize of the Ministry of Culture of Colombia
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
